## Commit Message Style

When creating git commits:

- Write clear, concise commit messages describing what changed and why
- **NEVER append** `Made-with: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Made with Cursor`, or any similar AI attribution tags to commit messages
- Do not add any footer lines referencing AI tools unless the user explicitly asks for it
